  <md:abstract>By the end of this section, you will be able to:
<list>
<item>Explain how hormonal cues help the kidneys synchronize the osmotic needs of the body</item>
<item>Describe how hormones like epinephrine, norepinephrine, renin-angiotensin, aldosterone, anti-diuretic hormone, and atrial natriuretic peptide help regulate waste elimination, maintain correct osmolarity, and perform other osmoregulatory functions</item>
</list></md:abstract>
