<content>
<para id="fs-idm47549440">While the kidneys operate to maintain osmotic balance and blood pressure in the body, they also act in concert with hormones. Hormones are small molecules that act as messengers within the body. Hormones are typically secreted from one cell and travel in the bloodstream to affect a target cell in another portion of the body. Different regions of the nephron bear specialized cells that have receptors to respond to chemical messengers and hormones. <link target-id="tab-ch41_05_01" document=""/> summarizes the hormones that control the osmoregulatory functions.</para>
